    <description>
            The Mars Science Laboratory (MSL) mission landed the mobile science
            laboratory Curiosity on Mars to assess the biological potential of the landing
            site, characterize the geology of the landing region, investigate
            planetary processes that influence habitability, and characterize
            the broad spectrum of radiation. This context product relates to the rover as
            a whole, rather than the individual instruments.
